[2] Philippines
Date: Mon 01 Sep 2008
Source: China View [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-09/01/content_9750579.htm>


A total of 195 deaths have been recorded caused by dengue in the
Philippines from January up to 02 Aug [2008], the country's health
agency said on Monday [01 Sep 2008]. Over the past months, around 19
658 dengue cases were recorded, compared to 22 028 in the same period
of last year, said Eric Tayag, chief of the Philippine National
Epidemiology Center. Among the 195 fatalities, 37 died in the
country's capital of Metro Manila.

Tayag said that in Metro Manila, there was a 3346 increase of dengue
cases, from last year's 2432 in the period. Tayag added that his
agency is now readying for a possible surge of dengue incidents with
the rainy season expected to peak in September and October [2008].

The health agency will closely monitor those flood-prone areas that
are vulnerable to the water-borne disease, he added.

[Byline: An, editor]

