[3] Viet Nam (Ca Mau)
Date: Sat 6 Sep 2008
Source: Nhan Dan [edited]
<http://www.nhandan.com.vn/english/life/060908/life_de.htm>


With the number of new patients of dengue fever 70 [to] 80 percent
lower than the number in July [2008] when the disease spread fastest,
the disease now is under control in the southern province of Ca Mau,
according to the province's Centre for Preventive Medicine.

Up to now [6 Sep 2008], nearly 5000 cases of dengue fever have been
reported in Ca Mau, including 7 fatal cases. The reason is poor rural
environmental sanitation, which created breeding grounds for
mosquitoes to multiply, causing the disease to spread quickly.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-MBDS Rapporteur Vern Weitzel

[In the previous posting on dengue in Viet Nam dated 31 Jul 2008, a
total of 3550 cases and 6 fatalities had been reported in Ca Mau
province (see prior ProMED archive no. 20080721.2211). At present,
there have been nearly 5000 cases and 7 deaths of dengue fever in
southern Ca Mau province.

36 900 cases and 33 deaths of dengue have been detected nationwide in
Viet Nam during 2008, with more than 6100 cases from Ho Chi Minh city
and more than 222 cases from Hanoi city (see ProMED archive no.
20080901.2739).

For maps of Viet Nam with provinces, see:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/vietnam_admin01.jpg> and:
<http://www.angelfire.com/co/hongnam/vnmap.html>.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Viet Nam can be accessed at:
