[4] Fiji
Date: Fri 05 Sep 2008
Source: Stuff.co.nz [edited]
<http://www.stuff.co.nz/stuff/4682248a34.html>


An outbreak of dengue fever has hit Fiji, one of New Zealand's main
tourist destinations. The country's Ministry of Health, Women and
Social Welfare has confirmed 9 cases have occurred in the past
fortnight. It said there have been no confirmed deaths but there has
been an increase in clinic visits and hospital admissions. Fiji joins
New Caledonia, Tonga, Kiribati and the Cook Islands [as localities
with dengue cases? - Mod. TY].

There is no vaccine available for dengue and the only preventative
measures available are insect repellent and long sleeved clothing,
particularly in the early evening. Mosquito nets are also recommended.

[Byline: Michael Field]

